We got boots, and maps, and guns on our backs, 

but we still can’t just behave ourselves. 

Even if to save our own lives, 

So Says I 

 A considerably mangled mishearing of a certain song.
附加记录：    

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


And thus, the product of countless hours of pouring over historical documents, maps, and photograph archives is finally complete. And if you get the beach reference, good for you.



+Spoilers

-Collapse



Go back and highlight sections of the article and look at what you can see.

Mouse over if you still don’t get it. SCP-5700-7 never died, he’s able to manipulate the flow of information about himself to the point where he can remove himself from recordings, documents, or memories. (Physical traces like footprints or food leftovers still remain.) He wiped specific memories of himself from SCP-5700-4 and SCP-57006 for his protection which is why they can only remember general details about him, and he has been traveling with SCP-5700-1 for decades, trying to find them a place to settle. Obviously, he allows SCP-5700-1 to be able to remember him and has tried to expunge himself from the Foundation’s records while also leaving behind enough tips to tell the Foundation he doesn’t want to be found even if they do catch on to the fact that he’s still alive.

And if you’re wondering about SCP-5700-3 “defeating the depths,” you’ll just have to wait for a Tale I have in the works ;)







